Listen in... You can hear the enemy team's voice chat with the Eavesdrop perk.
Be aware... You can spot enemy explosive devices like claymores and C4 with the Bomb Squad perk.

column3: holding marked objectives gives your team points.  The more objectives you hold

ppcc0t0t0: Watch those corners!  Be careful playing Search and Destroy - when you die you don't respawn.
Escort the bomb!  Protect the bomb carrier in Sabotage.  It takes teamwork to get to the enemy objective.
Call in radar!  You can earn radar for you and your team by getting 3 kills in a row without dying.
Call in an airstrike!  Get 5 kills in a row without dying and you can call in an air strike on the position of your choice.
Call in a chopper!  You can earn helicopter air support by getting 7 kills in a row without dying.
Back to basics... The Old School game modes don't have classes.  Everyone starts with the same weapons and must pick up new weapons and perks in the level.
Pick your shots!  When you fire a weapon WITHOUT a silencer
column3: you appear as a red dot on your enemies' compass.

ppcc0t0t0: Stealth technology.  Using the UAV Jammer perk will prevent you from showing as a red dot on the enemy compass.
Grenades from a rifle mounted grenade launcher need to travel before they are armed.  They do damage if they hit your enemy
column3: but only explode at a distance.

Use your inventory!  Items like grenade launchers
